This paper deals with an optimization problem with binary variables and linear objective functions, which is a classic topic in computer science. The focus of the paper is on enumerating the Pareto optima among the valid solutions, which is a problem in computational geometry and game theory. The paper also uses techniques from probability theory and analysis of algorithms, which are relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
